keyValuePair.Value: How important is winning the group?
You find yourselves in a great position. A good result here will be enough to take you through as group winners. How important would that be for %1s?
It's a chance to prove ourselves.
I think we're one of the strongest teams in the %1s this season. Let's put on a performance now to prove that, to ourselves and to everyone else.
It can push us on.
Winning the group would be making a statement. It would give everyone at the club a huge lift. I want us to do everything we can to make it happen.
That was always our target.
We set ourselves the target of winning the group right from the start. Let's do that and then we can turn our attention to the bigger prizes going forward.
Are you confident of qualifying?
Are you confident of qualifying?
It's been a decent run so far and you're just one win away from clinching qualification from your %1s group. Are you confident the boys can go out and get the result you need?

It's in our hands, right?
We've got ourselves into a good position. Getting into the knock-out rounds is in our hands now. I'm expecting the boys to do everything they can to make it happen.

It's what we should expect of ourselves.
This is a big club and we've been in decent form. I think getting out of the group should be the least we aim to do. I'm sure the boys will take advantage of the position we're in.
I expected more from us.
Yes, we're in pole position to qualify. But I'm disappointed. I think this team's good enough that we should have been aiming to win the group, to be honest. I expected better from the lads.
Are you confident you'll avoid being knocked out?
It's very tight in the group. You're now in a position where one defeat would see your boys eliminated. Can the team avoid that fate?
We have to take control.
I think we've been unlucky in games and with some of our results. The boys are still feeling confident. I think we can get a positive result here, for sure.
We've only ourselves to blame.
I'm frustrated we've got ourselves into this position. We've been patchy all through the group and we deserve to be where we are. Can we rescue the situation? I'm not sure.
It's been a great experience.
I'm not sure we'll qualify, but just to reach the %1s group stage has been a great experience for the boys. If we can't go any further, so be it.
